CLUSTERCTL()                                                      CLUSTERCTL()

NNAAMMEE
       cclluusstteerrccttll - Control a clustered application

       Control an application that has been clustered with strong-cluster-con-
       trol.

SSYYNNOOPPSSIISS
       slc clusterctl [options] [command]

OOPPTTIIOONNSS
       --hh, ----hheellpp
              print usage information

       --pp, ----ppaatthh, ----ppoorrtt <<ppaatthh>>
              cluster control socket to connect to, defaults to ..//cclluusstteerrccttll

       ccoommmmaanndd
              one of the supported commands, see below (defaults to ssttaattuuss)

       Supported commands are:

       +o   ssttaattuuss: report status of cluster workers, the default command

       +o   sseett--ssiizzee: set-size N, set cluster size to N workers

       +o   ssttoopp: stop the cluster controller

       +o   rreessttaarrtt: restart all workers

       Useful mostly for debugging:

       +o   ddiissccoonnnneecctt: disconnect all workers

       +o   ffoorrkk: fork one worker

EExxaammpplleess
       Run an app in the local directory, with two workers, and see status:

               slc example urlsaver my-url
               cd my-url
               slc run . --size=cpus &
               slc clusterctl # => print status of workers

       Get status on an app at a specific path:

               slc clusterctl -p /apps/my-app/clusterctl status

